g.text: RvE2 also has a very similar function as RvE1, however the latter was found to be a stronger activator of the receptor CMKLR1.

LTB4 would normally bind to its receptor LTB4R and consequently activate AKT1 and NFkB pathway. However, when RvE1 is present, it binds to the receptoor, therefore inhibitimng the binding of LTB4 and inhibiting the NFkB pathway as well.
